{
  "texts": [
    "Tools which generate high-level hypotheses and assist with ideation are largely based on language models.",
    "It is likely that targeted data generation (some of which may be synthetic) and reinforcement learning, along with the integration of reasoning models, will further develop capabilities here, but the former of these two may be challenging and expensive.",
    "Tools which generate more specific quantitative hypotheses to test, such as variations in protein sequences, are often driven by Bayesian models and protein language models or other general Global Risk Index for AI-enabled Biological Tools biological sequence models.",
    "Progress in these fields is likely to lead to a more optimised selection of test hypotheses, as well as better zero-shot prediction.",
    "Physical automated experimental systems are integrating increasingly large numbers of different workflow options and analytical techniques, allowing increasingly complex and diverse experimentation, and optimisation of the DBTL cycle of complex production tasks."
  ]
}